excerpt: Modern Buddhist pagoda featuring a large concrete Buddha statue atop a hill, offering city views.
detail_description: Long Son Pagoda is a modern Buddhist pagoda situated on a hill, offering stunning views of the city below. It is a symbol of Buddhism in the area and features a large concrete Buddha statue. Nearby attractions include the Po Nagar Cham Towers, Alexandre Yersin Museum, Nui Hon Chong beach, and Lanterns Cooking Class. Visitors can also explore local specialties at Dam Market and enjoy the beautiful scenery of the surrounding mountains and islands.
name: Long Son Pagoda
address: 22 Đ. 23 Tháng 10, Phương Sài, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: The city's main market, this busy 3-story building is densely packed with food & souvenir vendors.
detail_description: Situated in the northern part of Nha Trang on Ben Cho Street, Dam Market is a bustling 3-story building that stands as the city's main market. Its unique round shape and diverse array of stalls make it a must-visit for both locals and tourists. From household goods to handicrafts and souvenirs, this market offers an authentic glimpse into Vietnamese daily life.
name: Dam Market
address: Đường Đ. Phan Bội Châu, Vạn Thạnh, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: The Nha Trang Bishopric, also known as Nha Trang Cathedral or Stone Church, is a significant landmark in the city. Construction of this grand cathedral began in 1928 and was completed in 1941, showcasing its original Gothic architecture despite enduring harsh weather conditions. The cathedral holds great importance for the local parishioners as it serves as a place for prayer and reflection.
name: Tòa Giám Mục Nha Trang
address: 22 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Picturesque island known for its snorkelling & diving, beautiful beaches & unusual black rock.
detail_description: Hon Mun is a picturesque island known for its snorkeling and diving opportunities, beautiful beaches, and unique black rock formations. The island's high-rise cliffs feature dangerous wattles forming caves and grottoes in the southeast, with stones as black as ebony. Hon Mun is also famous for being a nesting site for flocks of swallows that migrate to the area every year.
name: Hon Mun
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Nha Trang is a coastal resort city in southern Vietnam known for its beaches, diving sites and offshore islands. Its main beach is a long, curving stretch along Tran Phu Street backed by a promenade, hotels and seafood restaurants. Aerial cable cars cross over to Hòn Tre Island, and the nature reserves of Hòn Mun and Hòn Tằm islands, reachable by boat, have coral reefs.
detail_description: Nha Trang, a stunning coastal resort city in southern Vietnam, is celebrated for its breathtaking beaches and vibrant diving spots. The main beach stretches gracefully along Tran Phu Street, flanked by a lively promenade filled with hotels and seafood eateries. Adventure seekers can take an aerial cable car to Hòn Tre Island or explore the coral-rich waters of nearby Hòn Mun and Hòn Tằm islands by boat.
name: Nha Trang
address: Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Historic scientific instruments & photos in a museum on the work of bacteriologist Alexandre Yersin.
detail_description: The Alexandre Yersin Museum in Nha Trang is a tribute to the renowned French-Swiss bacteriologist who made significant contributions to science, particularly in his research on the bubonic plague. Housed in Yersin's former residence, the museum showcases an extensive collection of original equipment, furniture, letters, and documents belonging to Yersin. Visitors can also explore a compelling array of photographs taken by Yersin during his travels around Vietnam.
name: Alexandre Yersin Museum
address: 10 Trần Phú, Vạn Thạnh, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Popular, family-friendly amusement park with rides, a water park & the world's longest cable car.
detail_description: Nha Trang's Vinpearl Land is a top-notch amusement park located on Hon Tre Island, accessible by one of the world's longest over-water cable cars. This family-friendly destination offers a wide array of attractions, including a water park, carnival rides, an aquarium, 4-D theaters, and more. Visitors can enjoy animal shows and musical performances with an all-in-one ticket that includes the gondola ride and unlimited access to entertainment.
name: Nha Trang - Vinpearl Land
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Vietnam

excerpt: Attraction with a scenic cluster of coastal boulders, swimming & traditional musical performances.
detail_description: Hon Chong is a must-visit attraction in Nha Trang, offering a scenic cluster of coastal boulders and a tranquil atmosphere, perfect for enjoying the sunset. Located at the foot of La San Hill, this unique rock setting is steeped in local legend and boasts a lovely mountainous coastline. The area attracts numerous visitors each year who come to admire the natural landscape and explore the beach for swimming or climbing on the rocks.
name: Hon Chong
address: Vĩnh Phước, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Lush, picturesque island featuring a number of beach resorts offering water sports & more.
detail_description: Hòn Tằm, also known as Tam Island, is a stunning and lush island located about 7km to the east of Nha Trang City in Vietnam. It is considered one of the most beautiful islands in the Nha Trang Bay area. The island offers a variety of beach resorts with picturesque natural landscapes and green trees. Visitors can enjoy water sports such as diving, parasailing, banana boat rides, and motorboating along the well-developed beach area.
name: Hòn Tằm
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: VinWonders Nha Trang, located on Pearl Island, is a comprehensive amusement park that offers a blend of resort facilities, dining options, and thrilling rides. The park features both water and land attractions with breathtaking views of Nha Trang Bay and the surrounding scenery. Visitors can enjoy various adventure activities and entertainment experiences without long queues.
name: VinWonders Nha Trang
address: Đảo Hòn Tre, Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Hòn Chồng is a unique and picturesque spot located north of Nha Trang's city center, offering stunning views of the surrounding mountains and sea. The beach is known for its clusters of large rocks that flow into the teal water, creating a one-of-a-kind seascape. Visitors can spend a relaxing day here swimming, walking along pathways, and admiring the gorgeous views while enjoying coffee.
name: Hòn Chồng
address: Vĩnh Phước, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: 3-story hilltop temple with 2 church towers offering historical exhibits & photos in a calm setting.
detail_description: Nestled on a serene hilltop just 3 kilometers north of Nha Trang, the Ponagar Temple complex is a captivating blend of history and spirituality. Constructed between the 7th and 12th centuries, this site features four remaining Cham towers, with the North Tower standing tall at an impressive height of 28 meters. The temple honors the goddess of land and serves as an active worship site for Cham, Chinese, and Vietnamese Buddhists alike.
name: Ponagar Temple
address: 61 Hai Tháng Tư, Vĩnh Phước, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: White-sand beach with calm bay waters & views of a nearby town with mountains in the distance.
detail_description: Bãi biển Nha Trang is a stunning beach destination known for its long stretches of white sand and calm, inviting waters. The area offers a variety of beach resorts and recreational activities, making it an ideal spot for a relaxing getaway. While the main beach may not be the most picturesque, it boasts convenient amenities such as a boardwalk, gardens, playgrounds, and sports facilities.
name: Bãi biển Nha Trang
address: Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Attraction with mischievous monkeys in the wild & circus-type shows, plus scuba diving spots.
detail_description: Monkey Island tourist resort, also known as Hon Lao, is a popular destination located just below the Ninh Van peninsula in the north of Nha Trang. The island is home to around a thousand mischievous monkeys that are unafraid of humans and will even interact with visitors by asking for food or taking their hands.
name: Monkey Island tourist resort
address: Lương Sơn, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Upbeat island with many entertainment options, from an amusement park & mall to a beach & mountain.
detail_description: Hon Tre Island, also known as Bamboo Island, is a vibrant destination in Nha Trang Bay offering a wide range of entertainment options. The island is home to Vinpearl Land Nha Trang, an expansive tourist attraction featuring a luxurious resort and a world-class amusement park. With its stunning location on one of the world's most beautiful bays, Hon Tre Beach boasts white sands and crystal-clear waters, providing visitors with the perfect setting for relaxation.
name: Hon Tre
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Discover the wonders of marine life at the Institute of Oceanography in Nha Trang. This research institute, with a history dating back almost a century, is located about 6km from the city center. It boasts an extensive collection of over 20,000 specimens representing more than 4,000 marine creatures and various other living organisms. While some visitors have noted that certain areas may need maintenance, the institute offers intriguing exhibits showcasing vibrant coral reefs and exotic sea creatures.
name: Institute of Oceanography
address: Số 1, Cầu Đá, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Tran Phu Beach, located in the heart of Nha Trang, is easily accessible from most parts of the city. The area along Tran Phu Street offers a range of accommodations, dining options, and vibrant nightlife including beach clubs and popular bars. Despite getting crowded during local fairs, the beach remains stunning with its strong yet beautiful waves. Visitors can enjoy a long stretch of clean sand lined with eateries and hotels.
name: Tran Phu Beach, Nha Trang
address: City, 86B Trần Phú, Vĩnh Hoà, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Nha Trang Beach is a popular destination in the province, offering a relaxed and laid-back atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy the tranquil surroundings and find shade under the palm trees. It's an ideal spot for families to unwind and take in the natural beauty of the area.
name: Bãi biển Nha Trang
address: 102 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Suoi Do Pagoda, a 50-year-old temple dedicated to the Chinese Goddess of Mercy, Quan Am, is located just a 30-minute drive from Nha Trang city center. The pagoda sits atop a mountain and can be reached by climbing around 200 stairs. Once there, visitors are rewarded with panoramic views of paddy fields, banana plantations, and neighboring hills.
name: Suoi Do Pagoda
address: Suối Hiệp, Diên Khánh, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Chic beachfront area known for its high-end boutique hotels & picturesque ocean surroundings.
detail_description: Ninh Van Bay is a secluded paradise situated on the Hon Mieu Peninsula, offering a perfect combination of opulence and natural splendor. The area is renowned for its upscale boutique hotels and stunning ocean vistas. It's an ideal destination for those seeking tranquility and relaxation away from the hustle and bustle of city life.
name: Ninh Van Bay
address: Ninh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Playful aquarium shaped like a giant sailing ship, showcasing a variety of fish & sea turtles.
detail_description: Tri Nguyen Aquarium is a must-visit attraction in Nha Trang, designed to resemble a giant sailing ship. This outdoor fish lake features rare marine species and live corals, creating an enchanting underwater experience. The aquarium offers various activities such as visiting the Tri Nguyen Fishing Village, exploring San Beach and Tranh Beach, as well as engaging in water sports like jet skiing and parasailing.
name: Tri Nguyen Aquarium
address: Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: The Vinpearl Cable Car is a popular choice for many tourists visiting the extraordinary Vinpearl Amusement Park. It's one of the longest cross-sea cable cars, spanning 3,320 meters (10,892 feet) from the mainland to Hon Tre island. The 15-minute ride offers breathtaking views of the ocean landscape and is a must-try experience with friends and family. The departure terminal is spacious with beautiful architecture and an uncovered parking lot, making it convenient for visitors.
name: VinPearl Cable Car
address: Trần Phú, Vĩnh Trường, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Cliff-jumping is the focus at this hike-through jungle hideaway with a variety of warm water pools.
detail_description: Ba Ho Waterfalls, located about 25 kilometers north of Nha Trang, is a hidden gem nestled in lush green wilderness. The journey to the waterfalls takes visitors through picturesque coastal waters and paddy fields. The area offers an exhilarating adventure with cliff-jumping and warm water pools for relaxation. Surrounded by dense jungle, it's a popular destination for hiking and climbing. Visitors can explore three different waterfalls, each offering its own unique experience.
name: Khu du lịch Ba Hồ
address: Thôn Vạn Thuận, Ninh Hòa, Khánh Hòa 57000, Vietnam

detail_description: Studio & Gallery Long Thanh Art in Nha Trang is a showcase of the captivating works of the renowned Vietnamese photographer, Long Thanh. His collection features powerful black-and-white portraits and landscapes that capture the essence of everyday life in Vietnam. Visitors have the opportunity to engage with Long Thanh himself and gain insight into the stories behind his compelling photographs. The gallery offers a wide range of prints for purchase, making it an ideal place to find a unique souvenir that reflects the soulfulness of Vietnam.
name: Studio & Gallery Long Thanh Art
address: 126 Hoàng Văn Thụ, Phương Sài, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Neo-Gothic church with an ornate bell tower, vaulted ceilings & colorful stained-glass windows.
detail_description: The Mountain Church, also known as the Stone Church, is a Neo-Gothic architectural gem located in Nha Trang. Built in 1933 on a 12-meter high mountain, it offers stunning views of the city. The church features an ornate bell tower, vaulted ceilings, and colorful stained-glass windows. Its Gothic style includes tall pillars, arched windows, and saint statues.
name: Mountain Church
address: 01 Thái Nguyên, Tân Tiến, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Vinpearl Land is a popular amusement park located on an island in Nha Trang Bay, Vietnam. It's part of VinGroup's extensive collection of hotels and resorts across the country. The park offers a wide range of attractions including rides, a water park, 4D movies, an aquarium, video games, and nightly water shows. With reasonable admission fees, it's suitable for both adults and families with children.
name: Vinpearl Land
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Lively place with shops & stalls selling clothing, footwear, souvenirs & other goods.
detail_description: Nha Trang Night Market is a must-visit destination in the coastal city of Nha Trang, Vietnam. Open from 5 - 6 pm until late at night, this vibrant market offers a lively atmosphere with hundreds of visitors exploring nearly 100 stalls selling a variety of goods including clothing, footwear, souvenirs, and street food such as grilled spring rolls and seafood dishes.
name: Night Market Nha Trang
address: Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Vietnam Active is a top choice for diving and snorkeling in Nha Trang, offering licensed PADI courses and tours to explore the stunning Nha Trang Bay. The bay boasts pristine islands and islets, making it an ideal destination for boat tours that often include snorkeling, visits to an aquarium, and fish farms. For those seeking a superb diving experience, Sailing Club Divers is worth considering. Rainbow Divers is another option for exploring Nha Trang's underwater wonders.
name: Vietnam Active - PADI 5 Star Diving Center & Snorkeling
address: 15 Đ. Nguyễn Trung Trực, Tân Tiến, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Stylish waterfront venue offering Indian, Vietnamese & Western fare, plus cocktails, DJs & dancing.
detail_description: Nestled along the stunning coastline, Sailing Club Nha Trang is a chic waterfront destination that seamlessly blends relaxation and vibrant nightlife. By day, it serves up an enticing array of Indian, Vietnamese, and Western dishes alongside refreshing cocktails. Guests can unwind on luxurious four-poster beds or beach deck chairs while soaking in breathtaking views of the East Sea.
name: Sailing Club Nha Trang
address: 72 74 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 570000, Vietnam

excerpt: Beachfront building & architectural landmark for its orange color & unique, lotus-like shape.
detail_description: Tháp Trầm Hương, also known as the Tram Huong Tower, is a striking architectural landmark located in the heart of Nha Trang. Its unique lotus-like shape and vibrant orange color make it an iconic symbol of this coastal city. The tower offers panoramic views of Nha Trang through telescopes installed inside, allowing visitors to enjoy the sea breeze while taking in the cityscape.
name: Tram Huong Tower
address: Trần Phú Quảng trường, Hai tháng Tư, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Turquoise coastal bay & beachfront known for its  boutique hotels & picturesque ocean surroundings.
detail_description: Nha Trang Bay is a stunning coastal destination known for its boutique hotels and picturesque ocean views. One of the main attractions in the area is Vinpearl Land Nha Trang, a complex tourist destination situated on Hon Tre island. This 200,000 square meter theme park features a 5-star resort, world-class amusement park, shopping street, food courts, and luxury restaurants.
name: Nha Trang Bay
address: Vietnam

excerpt: Exhibits include a whale skeleton & boat models, plus aquariums with tropical fish, turtles & more.
detail_description: Bảo Tàng Hải Dương Học, located south of the city and accessible via a scenic coastal highway, is a national oceanographic museum housed in a charming colonial-era building with French architecture. The exhibition features an impressive whale skeleton, aquariums showcasing sharks and tropical marine life, as well as various conservation and research areas to explore. This institute, established in the early 20th century, is one of Vietnam's oldest scientific research institutes focused on marine biodiversity and ecology.
name: Museum of Oceanography
address: 1 Cầu Đá - Hòn Một, Cầu Đá, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Relaxed outdoor place offering mud baths, hot baths & swimming pools, with several restaurants.
detail_description: Thap Ba Mud Bath is a popular destination in Nha Trang, offering visitors the chance to indulge in mud baths, hot baths, and swimming pools. Despite its unconventional nature, the mud is believed to have numerous health benefits such as promoting mineral absorption, exfoliating the skin, relieving stress and fatigue, and alleviating various ailments. This natural attraction is highly recommended for travelers seeking relaxation and rejuvenation after exploring Nha Trang.
name: THAP BA MUD BATH
address: 438 Ngô Đến, Ngọc Hiệp, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Tourism beach named for a noted revolutionary offering leisure, sailing, bars, hotels & spas.
detail_description: Trần Phú Beach, located in Nha Trang, is a vibrant destination known for its leisure activities, sailing opportunities, bars, hotels, and spas. The area is bustling with attractions such as souvenir shops, museums, resorts, and restaurants along Tran Phu Street. Adventure seekers can indulge in cycling, surfing, and snorkeling at the beach. Accessible from various parts of Nha Trang, it's considered one of the best beaches in the area.
name: Trần Phú
address: Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Buddha Park is located on a hilltop behind the Long Son Pagoda, featuring a large white Buddha seated on a lotus blossom, offering panoramic views of the city. The temple exudes tranquility and provides visitors with a serene and peaceful atmosphere to admire the impressive statue.
name: Buddha Park
address: 65M3+722, Vĩnh Thái, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

name: South Beach
address: An Viên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: The Do Dien Khanh Gallery, situated on Hong Bang street in Nha Trang, showcases the remarkable photography of Do Dien Khanh. Visitors can immerse themselves in his captivating portraits, landscapes, and everyday life photography that beautifully capture the essence of Vietnamese culture. If you're fortunate, you may even have the opportunity to be guided through the gallery by the talented photographer himself. Additionally, guests have the option to purchase prints of his stunning works.
name: Do Dien Khanh Gallery
address: 126B Đ. Hồng Bàng, Tân Tiến, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Protected diving & snorkeling area around Hòn Mun island featuring coral reefs & tropical fish.
detail_description: Hon Mun Marine Protected Area is a haven for diving and snorkeling enthusiasts, encompassing Hòn Mun island and several other surrounding islands. Covering a vast area of land and water, it aims to preserve the rich marine ecosystems and coral diversity of South Vietnam. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced diver, there are opportunities to explore the diverse underwater world here. For those seeking an adrenaline rush, diving at Octopus Rock promises an exhilarating experience amidst natural surroundings.
name: Hon Mun Marine Protected Area
address: 735 Nguyễn Tất Thành, Phước Đồng, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Nha Trang Station is conveniently located along the Thai Nguyen national road, providing direct access to Vietnam's northern and southern train lines. Travelers coming from Ho Chi Minh City or Da Nang can easily reach Nha Trang via this station. It offers the convenience of shipping scooters to other cities by train, with a reasonable fee based on the scooter model. The station also provides free WiFi for travelers.
name: Nha Trang Station
address: 17 Thái Nguyên, Tân Tiến, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nha Trang Center is a vibrant destination known for its stunning coastal beauty, with a long stretch of white sandy beach and a picturesque bay surrounded by lush hills. Visitors can explore historical Cham sites, indulge in seafood delights, and enjoy lively nightlife. The area offers various recreational activities such as water sports and mud bathing. Cho Dam provides an exciting shopping experience with an array of household items and local specialties.
name: Nha Trang Center
address: 20 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Nha Trang Evangelical Church, also known as the Stone Church, is a historic landmark in Nha Trang with over 80 years of history. Situated in the city center near the intersection of Nguyen Trai and Thai Nguyen streets, it boasts beautiful architecture reminiscent of French design. Visitors praise the warm and friendly congregation as well as the Christ-centered messages delivered during services.
name: Nha Trang Evangelical Church
address: 24 Đ. Lê Lai, Vạn Thạnh, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: I-Resort Nha Trang is the epitome of luxury and relaxation, offering a VIP package that includes a private mud-bath soak, mineral pool access, fruit platters, herbal tea or coffee, full-body massage, two-course meal, and a private bungalow stay. This upmarket resort features an outdoor water park, hot mineral mud baths, and a spa salon with various massage options.
name: Hot mineral springs I-Resort Nha Trang
address: 75CG+X3W, Tổ 19, thôn Xuân Ngọc, Vĩnh Ngọc, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Small island accessed by ferry, with seafood eateries in the village, beaches & an outdoor aquarium.
detail_description: Hon Mieu, also known as Mieu Island, is a small island in Nha Trang Bay that can be reached by ferry from Cau Da port. The island is densely populated and offers pristine beaches and the opportunity to visit two popular tourist destinations: Tri Nguyen Aquarium and Bai Beach Gravel. Tri Nguyen Aquarium features over 100 species of marine life, including live corals, and is designed in the shape of a fossil ship covered in moss.
name: Hon Mieu
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Skylight Nha Trang is a luxurious rooftop club located on the 45th floor of the Best Western Premier Havana Nha Trang hotel. It boasts an expansive space featuring 3 bars, 4 event areas, 3 DJ tables, and a stunning swimming pool. The club's glamorous decor exudes sophistication and style. Additionally, Skylight House offers an open-air complex with dining and entertainment spaces designed as a lighthouse on the hotel's 43rd floor.
name: Skylight & Lá Kitchen Nha Trang
address: Havana Nha Trang Hotel, 38 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Altitude Rooftop Bar is a must-visit spot in Nha Trang, offering not only delectable cuisine but also a breathtaking panoramic view of the city. The bar boasts an elegant and sophisticated architectural design that will surely captivate visitors upon arrival. Its spacious interior caters to various seating preferences, from plush sofas to a distinctive bar counter.
name: Altitude Rooftop Bar
address: Sheraton Nha Trang Hotel & Spa, 26-28 Trần Phú, Lộc Thọ, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

excerpt: Small, rocky beach popular for snorkeling & water sports as well as scenic mountain views.
detail_description: Bai Tranh Beach, located on Tri Nguyen Island in Nha Trang, is a popular destination for travelers seeking natural beauty and tranquility. The beach spans over 500 meters and offers untouched landscapes, white sand, and clear waters. It's a great spot for snorkeling and water sports with scenic mountain views. Despite being a public beach, it maintains a peaceful atmosphere away from the busier tourist areas. Visitors can also enjoy the Bai Tranh Beach Resort nearby.
name: Bai Tranh Beach
address: Vĩnh Nguyên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

excerpt: Covered bazaar with vendors selling regional produce, fruit & seafood, plus clothing & appliances.
detail_description: Xom Moi Market, located a bit away from downtown Nha Trang, offers an authentic local experience and delicious food. It's bustling with 1,150 vendors selling regional produce, seafood, clothing, and appliances. The market is a favorite spot for locals to shop for fresh foods and everyday needs at affordable prices. Visitors can enjoy breakfast prepared by locals and savor dishes like pho, fish soup with rice vermicelli, mango dessert, and thick noodle soup.
name: Xom Moi Market
address: 49 Đường Ngô Gia Tự, Tân Tiến, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Catamaran VN Yacht in Nha Trang offers an amazing sailing experience for special events and leisure trips. The yacht provides various activities such as snorkeling, paddling, and fishing, along with delicious food and stunning scenery. Guests can enjoy a sunset view while sipping on welcome drinks and champagne. The staff ensures safety at sea and creates a balanced atmosphere with music. Visitors are impressed by the beauty of the sea and nature, making it a memorable experience for friends and family.
name: Catamaran VN Yacht - Du thuyền tại Nha Trang
address: An Viên, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 650000, Vietnam

detail_description: Bãi biển Nhũ Tiên, located 10 km from Nha Trang's city center, is a serene escape known for its tranquil ambiance. The beach boasts a picturesque setting with lush mountains, white sandy shores adorned with coconut and palm trees, and clear turquoise waters. Unlike the bustling Tran Phu Beach in Nha Trang, Bãi biển Nhũ Tiên offers a peaceful retreat away from the city's hustle and bustle.
name: Bãi biển Nhũ Tiên
address: Phước Hạ, Phước Đồng, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa, Vietnam

detail_description: Rainbow Divers-Nha Trang is a diving center that offers an exceptional experience for divers. The instructors, such as Holly and Kha, are highly praised for their patience, friendliness, and professionalism. The crew on the dive boat is also commended for their hospitality. Divers appreciate the delicious provided meals and the shaded boat. The guides are helpful in assisting with material preparation and safety checks, ensuring a safe and enjoyable diving experience.
name: Rainbow Divers-Nha Trang
address: 132 Nguyễn Thiện Thuật, St, Nha Trang, Khánh Hòa 70000, Vietnam
